Package com.cafean.client.integrator

Class SubsystemIntegrator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.integrator.SubsystemIntegrator
  • public class SubsystemIntegrator
extends java.lang.Object
    The central class for the sub-system integration (master integrator) process. This class uses a list of AbstractIntegrator instances to create a list of CrossReferences that are used to reconnect references from outside an imported AbstractSubSystem.
    See Also:
    ImportSubsystemAction

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors

      SubsystemIntegrator​(AbstractSubSystem source, AbstractSubSystem target)
      Creates a sub-system integrator for use in importing the contents of the source sub-system into the target sub-system.

      • integrate

        public boolean integrate()
        This is the main method that performs the integration process described in the package documentation: find x-refs, copy all components, reconnect x-refs, etc.

        Note: findCrossReferences() must be called before this method or no references will be available to reconnect.

        Returns:
        false if any part of the integration process failed in a way that produced an error message.
